Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Damon. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 110.11. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1172)
